Ashoc Blue Raspberry tastes like a blue sno-cone with a heavy vanilla note on
the finish. It's actually really good. For $1.25 it's an amazing value
proposition and I easily pay more for almost everything Ashoc competes against,
which seems to be chiefly [[Celsius|Celsius_Raspberry_Acai_Green_Tea]] and
[[Ghost|Ghost_Energy_x_Welchs_Grape]]. Given the choice I'd buy this more often,
but it doesn't meaningfully differentiate itself from other options on the
shelf. Also it has extremely poor distribution, at least where I live, despite
heavy investment from Keurig Dr. Pepper. KDP actually [acquired a majority stake
in
Ghost](https://news.keurigdrpepper.com/2024-10-24-Keurig-Dr-Pepper-to-Acquire-Disruptive-Energy-Drink-Business-GHOST)
in 2024 and will acquire the remaining 40% stake in 2028, so I see why Ashoc is
not widely distributed anymore, if it ever was.

